# == Non-SI units used in atomic and nuclear physics ==
# - Quantity; Name of unit; Symbol for unit; Value in SI units (a)
# - Units accepted for use with the SI
# energy electronvolt (b) eV 1 eV = 1,602 176 487 (40) · 10-19 J
# mass dalton (c) Da 1 Da = 1,660 538 782 (83) · 10-27 kg
# unified atomic mass unit u 1 u = 1 Da
# length astronomical unit (d) ua 1 ua = 1,495 978 706 91 (6) · 1011 m
# - Natural units (n.u.)
# speed n.u. of speed (speed of light in vacuum) c0 299 792 458 m/s (exact)
# action n.u. of action (reduced Planck constant) h 1,054 571 628 (53) · 10-34 J s
# mass n.u. of mass (electron mass) me 9,109 382 15 (45) · 10-31 kg
# time n.u. of time h/(mec0 2) 1,288 088 6570 (18) · 10-21 s
# - Atomic units (a.u.)
# charge a.u. of charge, (elementary charge) e 1,602 176 487 (40) · 10-19 C
# mass a.u. of mass, (electron mass) me 9,109 382 15 (45) · 10-31 kg
# action a.u. of action, (reduced Planck constant) h 1,054 571 628 (53) · 10-34 J s
# length a.u. of length, bohr (Bohr radius) a0 0,529 177 208 59 (36) · 10-10 m
# energy a.u. of energy, hartree (Hartree energy) Eh 4,359 743 94 (22) · 10-18 J
# time a.u. of time h/Eh 2,418 884 326 505 (16) · 10-17 s


# ===== ISO 80000-11: Quantities and units — Part 11: Characteristic numbers =====

# == 4 Momentum transport ==
# 11-4.1 Reynolds number
# 11-4.2 Euler number
# 11-4.3 Froude number
# 11-4.4 Grashof number
# 11-4.5 Weber number
# 11-4.6 Mach number
# 11-4.7 Knudsen number
# 11-4.8 Strouhal number

# == 5 Transport of heat ==
# 11-5.1 Fourier number
# 11-5.2 Péclet number
# 11-5.3 Rayleigh number
# 11-5.4 Nusselt number
# 11-5.5 Biot number
# 11-5.6 Stanton number

# == 6 Transport of matter in a binary mixture ==
# 11-6.1 Fourier number for mass transfer
# 11-6.2 Péclet number for mass transfer
# 11-6.3 Grashof number for mass transfer
# 11-6.4 Nusselt number for mass transfer
# 11-6.5 Stanton number for mass transfer

# == 7 Constants of matter ==
# 11-7.1 Prandtl number
# 11-7.2 Schmidt number
# 11-7.3 Lewis number

# == 8 Magnetohydrodynamics ==
# 11-8.1 magnetic Reynolds number
# 11-8.2 Alfvén number
# 11-8.3 Hartmann number
# 11-8.4 Cowling number

# ===== ISO 80000-12: Quantities and units — Part 12: Solid state physics =====

# 12-1.1 lattice vector
# 12-1.2 fundamental lattice vectors
# 12-1.a metre

# 12-2.1 angular reciprocal lattice vector
# 12-2.2 fundamental reciprocal lattice vectors
# 12-2.a metre to the power minus one

# 12-3 lattice plane spacing
# 12-3.a metre

# 12-4 Bragg angle
# 12-4.a radian
# 12-4.b degree

# 12-5 order of reflexion
# 12-5.a one

# 12-6.1 short-range order parameter
